Enum RenderingType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<RenderingType>

    public enum RenderingType
extends java.lang.Enum<RenderingType>
    Defines the possible outcomes of rendering method calls.
    See Also:
    AsyncRenderingComponent, ImageRenderer, RenderingResult

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NO_RENDERING

        public static final RenderingType NO_RENDERING
        Means that no meaningful rendering was done by the renderer. The image to which it was drawing to should be discarded. Note that the render might have drawn something to the image but this should not be displayed to the user.

      • INSIGNIFICANT_RENDERING

        public static final RenderingType INSIGNIFICANT_RENDERING
        Means that the renderer did some rendering which should be displayed to the user but it is not significant. That is, it means that the rendered image does not contain what is the main interest of the user.

        For example: When displaying an image, this might mean that some meta information about the image to be rendered was drawn but the pixels of the image were not.

      • SIGNIFICANT_RENDERING

        public static final RenderingType SIGNIFICANT_RENDERING
        Means that the renderer did some rendering which should be displayed to the user and the rendering is significant to the user. That is, it means that the render image contains what is the main interest of the user.

        For example: When displaying an image, this might mean that the actual pixels of the image were drawn. Though, subsequent rendering might further enhance the image.
